Neurology VIII:  Degenerative diseases of the nervous system 

Learning tasks:
Know the pathology topics presented in Dr. Gujrati's lectures.
Describe the functional anatomy and causes of dementia.
Contrast minimal cognitive impairment with normal aging and Alzheimer's disease.
Describe the clinical manifestations, differential diagnosis, epidemiology and pathology of Alzheimer’s disease.
Describe clinical features of vascular dementia.
Describe  frontotemporal dementia and the related conditions of PSP and CBD, dementia with Lewy bodies, Normal pressure hydrocephalus and Creutzfeldt-Jokob disease(CJD).
Describe the epidemiology, clinical features, motor and nonmotor features, pathology and pathogenesis of Parkinson’s disease.
Describe essential tremor and contrast with Parkinson's disease.
Describe Huntington’s disease and levodopa-induced dyskinesia.
Describe the pathology, clinical features, epidemiology, and pathogenesis of ALS.

